<span class="headline">EQ Home Movies</span><br>
<span class="byline">4/4/01, 13:21 PST | <a href="mailto:kwill@rpgplanet.com">Kwill</a></span><br><br>
<span class="newsitem">Some cute movies from Skahld of <a href="http://www.gamersradionetwork.com/article.php?sid=53&mode=thread&order=0" target="_top">The Gamers Radio Network.</a><blockquote>Like Bombastika, I also have an addiction to EverQuest. I think I'll
                                         actually need professional therapy one day. But for now my
                                         therapy lies in multimedia.<br><br>

                                         During times of boredom or inspiration (sometimes one in the
                       same), I set up a web cam, ordered pizza and Mello yellow, and made some EverQuest
                       based movies.><br><br>

                       The first 2 are like EQ meets the Real World. Emperor Crush (an orc from Crushbone)
                       comes to stay with me for a few weeks. I plan to do more of these at some point, but I
                       am camera shy.</blockquote></span><br><br>
